<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued March 04 at 2:30PM MST until March 05 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Boise</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST
SUNDAY...
* WHAT...Snow. Accumulations of 2 to 4 inches in the Weiser Basin
and foothills in the western Magic Valley. The Camas Prairie,
West Central Mountains and Boise Mountains will see 3 to 6
inches in the valleys with 6 to 12 inches over the higher peaks.
Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.
* WHERE...Portions of south central, southwest and west central
Idaho.
* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Sunday. Heavier snow will occur late this
evening into the overnight.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and reduced
visibility. Winds will produce blowing and drifting snow.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.
The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.</instruction>
